  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Teacher training institutions improve the quality and inclusiveness of learning by accessing information and knowledge through ICTs</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The use of ICTs in education for interactive education and pedagogy that leads to information and knowledge richness is not yet adequately developed in Southern African region. Issues to address include: &#x2022;	Practicing teachers are not trained in effective use of ICTs in their teaching; &#x2022; There is a lack of digital pedagogy and &#x2022; Lack of access to suitable materials for diverse contexts. Training the required numbers of primary and secondary school teachers and students so that they become digitally skilled and effectively integrated to the ICT technology of the 21st century requires a collaborative effort.</narrative>
  </description>
